  <div xmlns:v="http://rdf.data-vocabulary.org/#" typeof="v:Review">
    <div class="main review-item" id="7559092">
        

  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/7559092/" class="title-link">知行合一的“知”</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-7559092"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/50508828/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u50508828-2.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/50508828/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">阿汤哥</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2015-08-04"
      class="main-meta">2015-08-04 12:31:53</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_7559092_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  王阳明的知行合一的“知”，是不是我们现代所说的“认知”呢？ “认知”，西方近代哲学讲得很多，特别是康德。王阳明所说的“知”，我认为主要还是指中国传统的“道德意识”吧，因为中国哲学家的目的就是要成“圣人”。 中共对心学不太重视，特别是对于“良知”，是用它的那个...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/7559092/#comments">(1回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">0有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_7559092_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_7559092_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>





